<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="400" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="7" pageNumber="400">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1719,2006]" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">
<keyLead pageId="7" pageNumber="400">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,163,1719,1740]" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">1</emphasis>
. Head rounded in anterior view; ventral margin of clypeus slightly projecting over mandibles (
<figureCitation box="[1148,1228,1720,1742]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,345,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-90@4.[151,1436,345,1870]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Fumariphilus versicolor, n. comb., SEM photos of a female. (A) Head, anterior view. (B) Head, posterior view. (C) Antenna. (D) Mesosoma, dorsal view. (E) Mesosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683376" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683376/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Notauli weekly impressed but visible in anterior one third of mesoscutum; median mesoscutal impression visible posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[1256,1334,1749,1771]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,345,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-90@4.[151,1436,345,1870]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Fumariphilus versicolor, n. comb., SEM photos of a female. (A) Head, anterior view. (B) Head, posterior view. (C) Antenna. (D) Mesosoma, dorsal view. (E) Mesosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683376" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683376/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
). Scutellar foveae with some irregular rugae; mesoscutum with coriaceous, dull sculpture; mesoscutellum with rugose sculpture (
<figureCitation box="[1349,1426,1778,1800]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,345,1869]" captionTargetId="figure-90@4.[151,1436,345,1870]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Fumariphilus versicolor, n. comb., SEM photos of a female. (A) Head, anterior view. (B) Head, posterior view. (C) Antenna. (D) Mesosoma, dorsal view. (E) Mesosoma, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683376" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683376/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
). Forewing with absent areolet; Rs vein reaching anterior margin of wing. Galls in fruits of species of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Nieves-Aldrey" baseAuthorityYear="2003" box="[1191,1275,1808,1829]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Papaveraceae" genus="Fumaria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="7" pageNumber="400" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1191,1275,1808,1829]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">Fumaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
........................................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="(Nieves-Aldrey)" authorityName="Nieves-Aldrey" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Nieves-Aldrey" baseAuthorityYear="1985" box="[1147,1436,1836,1859]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Fumariphilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="400" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="versicolor">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1147,1436,1836,1859]" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1147,1269,1836,1858]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">F. versicolor</emphasis>
(Nieves-Aldrey)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1719,2006]" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">
<keyLead pageId="7" pageNumber="400">
- Head trapezoid in anterior view; ventral margin of clypeus distinctly projecting over mandibles (
<figureCitation box="[1156,1232,1866,1888]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,524,1936]" captionTargetId="figure-160@6.[151,1437,524,1937]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Fumariphilus hypecoi, n. comb., SEM photos of a female. (A) Head, dorsal view. (B) Head, posterior view. (C) Head, anterior view. (E) Mesosoma, dorsal view. (E) Antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683380/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). Notauli narrow and shallow, clearly visible only in posterior one third of mesoscutum, faint anteriorly; median mesoscutal impression absent (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,524,1936]" captionTargetId="figure-160@6.[151,1437,524,1937]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Fumariphilus hypecoi, n. comb., SEM photos of a female. (A) Head, dorsal view. (B) Head, posterior view. (C) Head, anterior view. (E) Mesosoma, dorsal view. (E) Antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683380/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
). Scutellar foveae shallow, smooth and shining. Mesoscutum delicately shining coriaceous; mesoscutellum delicately alutaceous medially, with concentric rugae laterally (
<figureCitation box="[708,786,1954,1976]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[151,1437,524,1936]" captionTargetId="figure-160@6.[151,1437,524,1937]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Fumariphilus hypecoi, n. comb., SEM photos of a female. (A) Head, dorsal view. (B) Head, posterior view. (C) Head, anterior view. (E) Mesosoma, dorsal view. (E) Antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683380/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
). Forewing with a visible triangle shaped areolet; Rs vein not quite reaching anterior margin of wing (
<figureCitation box="[556,631,1983,2006]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1519,1543]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1495]" captionTargetId="figure-18@7.[151,1436,181,1495]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Habitus, forewing and terminal instar larvae of Fumariphilus hypecoi, n. comb. (A), (C), (E) and Fumariphilus versicolor, n. comb. (B), (D) and (F). All in lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6683384" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6683384/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
). Galls in fruits of 
<taxonomicName box="[813,998,1984,2006]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Papaveraceae" genus="Hypecoum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="7" pageNumber="400" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[813,916,1984,2005]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">Hypecoum</emphasis>
species.
</taxonomicName>
.................... 
<taxonomicName authority="(Trotter)" authorityName="Nieves-Aldrey" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Trotter" baseAuthorityYear="1913" box="[1240,1436,1983,2005]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Fumariphilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="400" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hypecoi">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1240,1436,1983,2005]" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1240,1341,1983,2005]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="400">F. hypecoi</emphasis>
(Trotter)
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
